<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-11T17:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-11T17:49:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/62.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-11T18:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your November 12. Commission has full powers: first, to arrange the
                            details of operations of the treaty; second, to settle, with the good
                            offices of the Government of the United States, all differences between
                            the Haitian Government and third parties; third, to negotiate, with the
                            good offices of the Government of the United States, all loans necessary
                            to attain the aims of the treaty; fourth, to decide upon some plan to
                            establish the Haitian finances on a firm basis.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>